trMA.AposIdiomelon1.text = "The beauty of abstinence has shined, chasing away the dingyness of demons. The solemnity of the fast has appeared, bringing with it the healing of the passions of our souls. Daniel and the children in Babylon armed themselves with fasting long ago; the one shut the mouths of lions, while the others quenched the flame of the furnace. With them, save us also by fasting, O Christ our God, as the lover of mankind."
trMA.AposMartyric.text = "You shine as luminaries in the world even after death, O holy Martyrs, having fought the good fight. Therefore, having boldness of speech, entreat Christ to have mercy on our souls."
trMA.AposTheotokion.text = "O Holy one among women, Theotokos, Mother unwedded: intercede with the King and God whom you bore, that he may save us, as he is the lover of mankind."
trVE.AposIdiomelon1.text = "The springtime of the feast has dawned, the flower of repentance! So let us purify ourselves, brethren, from all impurity. Chanting to the giver of life, let us say: Glory to you, O only lover of mankind."
trVE.AposMartyric.text = "Your Martyrs, O Lord, being strengthened by faith, confirmed by hope, and united in spirit by the love of your Cross, destroyed the enemy's tyranny and received crowns. With the bodiless hosts, they intercede for our souls."
trVE.AposTheotokion.text = "Exalted Lady first in holiness, since you are the praise of the heavenly Orders, the song of the Apostles, and the explanation of the Prophets, accept also our fervent prayers."
